### Describe the bug

After upgrading to hibernate 6, the `QueryCacheKey` constructor fails due to the query parameter's name being now null. Switching to position doesn't help as that also returns a null value.

This code was put in place in the quarkus3 branch to be able to start Keycloak with the map store: (`JpaMapKeycloakTransaction.QueryCacheKey`)

```
            for (Parameter<?> parameter : query.getParameters()) {
                // HACK TO GET KC TO START WITH NEW STORE - HAS TO BE FIXED AS SOME SEARCHES USE A DIFFERENT EXPRESSIBLE IMPL
                JpaCriteriaParameter criteriaParameter = (JpaCriteriaParameter) parameter;
                SqmBasicValuedSimplePath expressible = (SqmBasicValuedSimplePath) criteriaParameter.getExpressible();
                String parameterName  = expressible.getNavigablePath().getLocalName();
                if (parameterName == null) {
                    throw new ModelException("Can't prepare query for caching as parameter doesn't have a name");
                }
                this.queryParameters.put(parameterName, ((JpaCriteriaParameter<?>) parameter).getValue());
            }
```

We need to figure out how to properly handle this as the above hack won't work in all scenarios.

### Version

quarkus3 branch

### Expected behavior

QueryCacheKey should be able to retrieve the query parameter names.

### Actual behavior

QueryCacheKey obtains names using explicit type casts that won't always work.

### How to Reproduce?

Use quarkus3 branch

